Definition: chronic granulomatous communicable disease occurring in tropical and subtropical regions
Example: characterized by inflamed nodules beneath the skin and wasting of body parts; caused by the bacillus Mycobacterium leprae
Synonyms: adj, pert, leprous, Hansen, s_disease, infectious_disease, chronic, granulomatous, communicable, disease, occurring, in, tropical, and, subtropical, regions, characterized, by, inflamed, nodules, beneath, the, skin, wasting, of, body, parts, caused, bacillus, Mycobacterium, leprae
Category: noun.state
